Description.TranslatedText: Parameters used to describe the time-concentration curve.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, from dosing to end of the current collection interval.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Amount Recovered

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, from dosing to end of the current collection interval divided by the body mass index.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Amount Recovered Normalized by Body Mass Index

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, from dosing to end of the current collection interval divided by the dose.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Amount Recovered Normalized by Dose

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, from dosing to end of the current collection interval divided by the surface area.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Amount Recovered Normalized by Surface Area

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, from dosing to end of the current collection interval divided by the weight.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Amount Recovered Normalized by Weight

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The percentage of the area under curve extrapolated to infinity that was due to back extrapolation to estimate concentration at time zero, based on the observed value for concentration at time zero.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Observed Area Under the Curve Percent Back Extrapolation

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The percentage of the area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity that was due to back extrapolation to estimate concentration at time zero, based on the predicted value for concentration at time zero.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Predicted Area Under the Curve Percent Back Extrapolation

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The percentage of the area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity from Tlast to infinity based on the observed value for concentration at TLast.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Observed Area Under the Curve Percent Extrapolation

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The percentage of the area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity from Tlast to infinity based on the predicted value for concentration at TLast.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Predicted Area Under the Curve Percent Extrapolation

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Area Under the Curve All

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation divided by the body mass index, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: AUC All Normalized by Body Mass Index

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation divided by the dose, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation divided by the surface area, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation divided by the weight, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.
